{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"09beb690-44e0-11ed-818e-9566cf446af0","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rowsAreFullWidth":false,"backgroundImageUrl":"","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"41003885-b756-4bcb-ac87-5fc09f618870","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Additional Consequences of Leverage: Agency Costs and Information","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"ab0e6c55-f006-4e7e-8c8d-da2571b5b76b"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":31},"ref":"5d26981c-7b96-49c0-a76f-b3da9a6ee179","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"c9ba9d3a-c31d-45d9-9ce4-53f1bba050d1","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"cba7cb3d-527a-4364-b74b-18c5bcc00c80","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Dynron Corporation’s primary business is natural gas transportation using its vast gas pipeline network. Dynron’s assets currently have a market value of $150 million. The firm is exploring the possibility of raising $50 million by selling part of its pipeline network and investing the $50 million in a fiber-optic network to generate revenues by selling high-speed network bandwidth. Whereas this new investment is expected to increase profits, it will also substantially increase Dynron’s risk. If Dynron is levered, would this investment be more or less attractive to equity holders than if Dynron had no debt?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"4755dfab-bb7f-4751-a496-9206755cce70","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"61edca81-85fa-482e-8edd-49e6202f1eff","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Consider a firm whose only asset is a plot of vacant land, and whose only liability is debt of $15 million due in one year. If left vacant, the land will be worth $10 million in one year. Alternatively, the firm can develop the land at an up-front cost of $20 million. The developed land will be worth $35 million in one year. Suppose the risk-free interest rate is 10%, assume all cash flows are risk-free, and assume there are no taxes.","marks":[]}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"a","startValue":1},"ref":"9ea7b2e4-442e-4525-b55c-7fbf264fb123","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"2c7e510a-125c-4ce3-af63-c02badf8a674","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"2e970f99-0360-4340-bd4d-af0bce2d0a3e","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"If the firm chooses not to develop the land, what is the value of the firm’s equity today? What is the value of the debt today?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"2df6ae47-3a86-4580-bb01-bf6717f4ede5","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"d1564efb-fd60-4b58-9e0d-46e5591b3d9c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What is the NPV of developing the land?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"46225b14-5292-409b-8875-6e666943f7d5","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"907ac004-2a5f-423c-af23-6774c2737836","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Suppose the firm raises $20 million from equity holders to develop the land. If the firm develops the land, what is the value of the firm’s equity today? What is the value of the firm’s debt today?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"4aaf916d-ec0e-43b7-bdaa-617a6a8c85d4","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"a172ff3c-78b0-4147-ad2b-7af68def942c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Given your answer to part (c), would equity holders be willing to provide the $20 million needed to develop the land?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"97e1bade-8dd2-4c7e-b26b-7c73b5b905ec","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"def458b9-9eeb-46bd-92bb-0e78841b08af","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Zymase is a biotechnology start-up firm. Researchers at Zymase must choose one of three different research strategies. The payoffs (after taxes) and their likelihood for each strategy are shown below. The risk of each project is diversifiable.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"f0d1a2d1-5e18-426e-9b6a-fd6ceaf05141"}]}]},{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-table","config":{"activityLabel":"","instructions":"","tableCaptionText":"","activityTitle":"","tableTitle":"","captions":"","credit":""},"value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{},"nodes":[{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Strategy","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"fce9efa4-1023-4b0b-a784-f4689e087154"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Probability","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"a0f2990d-de6f-4421-adc8-0f116c3b49b6"},{"data":{"colSpan":1,"rowSpan":1},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Payoff ($ million)","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"object":"block","type":"table-header","ref":"ce795e87-65e5-45e2-b644-db1541b8e922"}],"object":"block","type":"table-row","ref":"b